  <h2>What is a shuffle??</h2>
  <iframe src="https://giphy.com/embed/pketYkIQQkMO4" width="480" height="353" frameBorder="0"></iframe>
</section>
<section>
  <h2>Distributed computing worst best when executors work indepedently.</h2>
  <p>
  <br><br>
  Shuffles are operations when the executors <b>CANNOT</b> workly indepedently.  
  <br><br>
  A shuffle is when your executors must communicate with the driver (and each other).
  <br><br>
  Joins, GroupBys, Window functions, Repartitions, Aggregations.
  </p>
</section>
